DESCRIPTION: Designated on October 1966, Natural Landmark status was given to this area because of the Mojave Desert Joshua Tree vegetation association. The most dominant and dramatic of the plants in this association is the Joshua Tree (Yucca breviflora).

FET_NAME: White River Enron Boat Ramp Campsites

DESCRIPTION: A group site camping area where there are 4 group sites at $50/night and 3 individual sites that are $15/night. A large overflow parking area is located here as well.
Lower area has two group sites at $50/night
This campground consists of 11 individual sites at $15/night. Six of these sites also contain a tent pad. Six sites also contain a shade structure.
This campground offers 6 individual sites at $15/night. Each site contains a fire ring, picnic table, and two corrals for horses.
Upper Campground has 12 individual sites at $15/night and one group site at $50/night
This campground contains 6 individual sites at a fee of $15/night.
